;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:39:"http://ma.tt/2010/07/10-reasons-for-wp/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:325:"<p>Adam Schwartz writes <a href="http://www.computercourage.com/2010/07/21/top-10-reasons-to-use-wordpress-org-for-your-website/">Top 10 Reasons To Use WordPress.org For Your Website</a>, in case you needed a summary. <img src="http://s.ma.tt/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 23 Jul 2010 16:06:42 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:28;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"Matt: Web Designer Magazine Interview";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=35193";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"http://ma.tt/2010/07/web-designer-magazine-interview/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:876:"<p><a href="http://s.ma.tt/files/2010/07/wd167-small.jpg"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-35195" title="wd167-small" src="http://s.ma.tt/files/2010/07/wd167-small-165x212.jpg" alt="" width="165" height="212" /></a></p>\n<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>Q. If you had a crystal ball would you have given more thought to the commercial aspects that WordPress has to offer?</p></blockquote></div>\n<p>A few months ago I did an interview with Web Designer magazine they just published on the web as<a href="http://www.webdesignermag.co.uk/interviews/the-wizard-of-wordpress-an-interview-with-matt-mullenweg/">The Wizard of WordPress, An interview with Matt Mullenweg</a>. It includes the answer to the above question. They published it with a funky Warhol-esque cover, but I can&#8217;t find an image of that online. (Issue 167 isn&#8217;t listed on their site.)</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 22 Jul 2010 20:36:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:29;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress 3.0 – 10 Million Downloads and Counting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2010/07/21/wordpress-3-0-10-million-downloads-and-counting/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2010/07/21/wordpress-3-0-10-million-downloads-and-counting/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1571:"<p><a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/wordpresslogoofficial.png" rel="thumbnail"><img class="wlDisabledImage" title="wordpresslogoofficial" border="0" alt="wordpresslogoofficial" align="left" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/wordpresslogoofficial_thumb.png" width="100" height="100" /></a></p>\n<p>About a month ago I posted about <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2010/06/20/wordpress-3-0-moving-fast/">how fast WordPress 3.0 was being downloaded</a> and there was a terrific discussion about the sheer amount of data that was being grabbed to get at the 3.0 version of WordPress.&#160; We even had some comments as to why it was being downloaded at that scale.</p>\n<p>Well as of today the <a href="http://wordpress.org/download/counter/">download counter</a> reads that it has been downloaded just over 10.3 million times since it was released last month and the counter keeps rolling along!</p>\n<p>So what is it that makes the WordPress platform so popular?&#160; What is it that drives people to download it over 10 million times?</p>\n<p>If you had the opportunity to talk to a non WordPress user what would you tell them about it to show that it is worth downloading and putting to use for a website?</p>\n<p>What is your favorite thing about WordPress?&#160; What is your least favorite thing about it?&#160; What would you add to it?</p>\n<p>The experience of this community is the perfect forum to start a dialog like this so I am looking forward to seeing everyone’s thoughts.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 21 Jul 2010 22:23:00 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Richard Hay";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:30;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"bbPress: 2010-07-21 Meetup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"http://bbpress.org/?p=373";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"http://bbpress.org/blog/2010/07/2010-07-21-meetup/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13252:"<p>IRC log from the meetup on July 21, 2010</p>\n<p><span id="more-373"></span>[21:02:40 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    &lt;meetup&gt;<br />\n[21:02:58 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Hi <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:03:05 GMT]    =-=    Nightgunner5 is now known as jjj5<br />\n[21:03:09 GMT]    &lt;jjj5&gt;    Hi, jjj!<br />\n[21:03:10 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Haha<br />\n[21:03:15 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    @ben jjjjj<br />\n[21:03:30 GMT]    &lt;jjj5&gt;    [11:37:02am] &lt;jjj3&gt; we should do the dev chat with jjj-jjj5<br />\n[21:03:30 GMT]    &lt;jjj5&gt;    [11:37:09am] &lt;jjj3&gt; that would be make up for some interesting logs<br />\n[21:03:52 GMT]    &#8211;&gt;|    SHRIKEE (~arnan@a91117.upc-a.chello.nl) has joined #bbpress<br />\n[21:04:10 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Oh come on now&#8230; I&#8217;m not *that* good of a developer where I need to be cloned. <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:04:20 GMT]    =-=    jjj5 is now known as Nightgunner5<br />\n[21:04:22 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    Fine <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:04:26 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Hahaha<br />\n[21:04:34 GMT]    &lt;SHRIKEE&gt;    but now youre only half as good<br />\n[21:04:37 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Probably better off with more Nightgunners and chrishajer&#8217;s anyhow <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:05:11 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    ch^5<br />\n[21:05:29 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    Gautam is asleep?<br />\n[21:05:38 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    So obviously todays meetup is going to be fairly relaxed. Since we&#8217;re just getting started I figured we&#8217;d have an open discussion.<br />\n[21:06:01 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Yeh I think so. We can always reschedule the next meeting around what works for everyone.<br />\n[21:06:51 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    does anyone need anything?<br />\n[21:07:03 GMT]    &lt;SHRIKEE&gt;    yup<br />\n[21:07:22 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Cocktails? Snacks? <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:07:35 GMT]    &lt;SHRIKEE&gt;    snacks == win<br />\n[21:07:58 GMT]    &#8211;&gt;|    r-a-y (~r-a-y@S0106001346ef7dff.vs.shawcable.net) has joined #bbpress<br />\n[21:08:09 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    beverage?<br />\n[21:08:27 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    chrishajer: Eventually we will need more eyes on the plugin code. Gautam&#8217;s already found a few little things.<br />\n[21:08:39 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Mostly copy/pasta<br />\n[21:08:47 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    Hey, I fixed one word<br />\n[21:09:12 GMT]    &lt;SHRIKEE&gt;    mmm pasta<br />\n[21:09:44 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    chrishajer: Do you want to bring us up to speed with where 1.1 is?<br />\n[21:09:55 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    all -<br />\n[21:10:23 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    1.1 is right here: http://trac.bbpress.org/browser/trunk<br />\n[21:10:27 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    1.1 should be packaged up and released, so we can stop answering stupid questions about things that are broken in 1.0.2 and are already fixed in 1.1 (or if you want to call it, 1.0.3)<br />\n[21:10:39 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    1.1 I think has one open bug?<br />\n[21:10:52 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    it&#8217;s far better than 1.0.2 is<br />\n[21:11:33 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    this one for sure before release http://trac.bbpress.org/ticket/1301<br />\n[21:11:33 GMT]    &lt;trac-bot&gt;    chrishajer: http://trac.bbpress.org/ticket/1301 critical/high, 1.0.3, Nightgunner5-&gt;(no owner), reopened, Fix for incorrect order of posts and for posts being displayed twice<br />\n[21:11:34 GMT]    &lt;r-a-y&gt;    There are three tickets left in 1.0.3 &#8211; http://trac.bbpress.org/query?status=assigned&amp;status=new&amp;status=reopened&amp;group=status&amp;milestone=1.0.3<br />\n[21:11:42 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    yeah<br />\n[21:11:57 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    Oh right, that&#8217;s the one Gautam wanted me to fix<br />\n[21:11:58 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    1313 and 1317 are very new tickets<br />\n[21:12:09 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    we&#8217;re talking about fixing year old bugs<br />\n[21:12:18 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    which ARE fixed in 1.1 now<br />\n[21:12:22 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    but broken in 1.0.3<br />\n[21:12:35 GMT]    &lt;r-a-y&gt;    chris: Ahh okay, just joined the room. Apologies.<br />\n[21:12:54 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Does it make sense to skip 1.0.3? or are there too many changes in 1.1 to make upgrading easy?<br />\n[21:13:03 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    jjj<br />\n[21:13:14 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    Matt said skip 1.0.3, get 1.1 out the door if it&#8217;s ready<br />\n[21:13:23 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Cool.<br />\n[21:14:06 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    From Matt to me May 27 &#8220;I don&#8217;t think we should update the 0.9 branch anymore, and probably not 1.0 either. (Same as WP.) If 1.1 is ready let&#8217;s get it out the door. <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> &#8221;<br />\n[21:14:25 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Makes sense to me!<br />\n[21:14:25 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    so, I think the plan is 1.1 (since the 1.0.3 milestone was deleted anyway)<br />\n[21:14:35 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    at least 1301 should be fixed<br />\n[21:14:48 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    not sure what&#8217;s involved in 1313 and 1317<br />\n[21:15:22 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    1317 is easy<br />\n[21:15:28 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    re going from 1.0.2 to 1.0.3, it&#8217;s no problem, but a moot point. There was only one minor DB schema change, and that was very recent. But you can upgrade 1.0.2 to 1.0.3 or 1.1 without a problem<br />\n[21:15:35 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    that&#8217;s not programmer talk!<br />\n[21:15:38 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    easy &#8211; pfft<br />\n[21:16:15 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    #1313 makes sense at a glance also.<br />\n[21:16:16 GMT]    &lt;trac-bot&gt;    jjj: http://trac.bbpress.org/ticket/1313 major, 1.0.3, bobrik-&gt;(no owner), new, Wrong looping through terms objects<br />\n[21:16:45 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    so, let&#8217;s make it 1.1 and let&#8217;s fix the last couple tickets and then be done with 1.1 &#8211; as good as bbPress 1.x in this format (non-plugin)<br />\n[21:17:00 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    hmm,<br />\n[21:17:03 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    there&#8217;s a patch?<br />\n[21:17:06 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    didn&#8217;t catch that<br />\n[21:17:10 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    I will test that one<br />\n[21:17:14 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Yep. Patches clean but needs an indent.<br />\n[21:18:04 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    So #1301 is the only one that needs attention.<br />\n[21:18:04 GMT]    &lt;trac-bot&gt;    jjj: http://trac.bbpress.org/ticket/1301 critical/high, 1.0.3, Nightgunner5-&gt;(no owner), reopened, Fix for incorrect order of posts and for posts being displayed twice<br />\n[21:18:27 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    after the two easy ones <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:18:51 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    I figured out the problem and I&#8217;m working on it<br />\n[21:18:58 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    That&#8217;s the status though<br />\n[21:19:03 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    1.1 is nearly ready to go<br />\n[21:19:10 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    fixes some long-standing bugs<br />\n[21:20:19 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Awesome.<br />\n[21:20:48 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    need me for anything else?<br />\n[21:20:52 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    ETA on 1.1 then? By next week, considering testing, etc&#8230;?<br />\n[21:21:04 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    depends on Ben&#8217;s patch I think<br />\n[21:21:09 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    k<br />\n[21:21:35 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    chrishajer: Are you in on 1.2? I haven&#8217;t really seen you chime in much about it all.<br />\n[21:21:54 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    I forget how to do &#8220;private&#8221;<br />\n[21:22:03 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    :shrug:<br />\n[21:22:45 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    http://nightgunner5.is-a-geek.net:1337/oh-gosh-lets-just-get-this-over-with.txt<br />\n[21:22:57 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    haha<br />\n[21:23:06 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    rock on<br />\n[21:23:08 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    On the upside, it works perfectly now. On the downside, I used regular expressions.<br />\n[21:23:39 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    what does the regex do (in Engrish?)<br />\n[21:24:00 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    It finds out what to put the posts in order by<br />\n[21:24:45 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    ORDER BY &#8220;entertainment value&#8221; <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" class="wp-smiley" /><br />\n[21:24:53 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    not what you would consider the &#8220;correct way&#8221; though?<br />\n[21:25:19 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    ORDER BY &#8216;troll value&#8217; ASC<br />\n[21:25:37 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    Well, there&#8217;s the saying &#8216;Some people, when confronted with a problem, think &#8220;I know, I&#8217;ll use regular expressions.&#8221; Now they have two problems.&#8217;<br />\n[21:25:44 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    chrishajer: ping me later if you want to chat<br />\n[21:25:47 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    I like that expression<br />\n[21:25:59 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    @jjj &#8211; email me if you need anything<br />\n[21:26:08 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    chrishajer: Will do<br />\n[21:26:23 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    so, we will have two patches for 3 bugs?<br />\n[21:26:28 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    I will let Gautam know<br />\n[21:26:29 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    OH<br />\n[21:26:30 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    jjj<br />\n[21:26:36 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Yessum<br />\n[21:26:54 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    for some reason, with Gautam, when you give him props, it comes up ? like GautamGupta?<br />\n[21:27:03 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    he has some weird issue with his username<br />\n[21:27:04 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    anyway<br />\n[21:27:08 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    to get around the ?<br />\n[21:27:13 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Yeah you have to ! before it<br />\n[21:27:14 GMT]    &lt;Nightgunner5&gt;    Trac thinks it&#8217;s a wiki page that doesn&#8217;t exist<br />\n[21:27:18 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    you can do ! like !GautamGupta<br />\n[21:27:20 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    right<br />\n[21:27:25 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    @ben<br />\n[21:27:37 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    Didn&#8217;t know his name came up like that, will do from now on though.<br />\n[21:27:40 GMT]    &lt;chrishajer&gt;    there is some weird thing with his username. he changed it or something<br />\n[21:27:54 GMT]    &lt;jjj&gt;    ty <img src="http://bbpress.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D"